org.jsapar.model

Class LineUtils

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.jsapar.model.LineUtils

  • public class LineUtils
extends Object
    Utility functions for Line that simplifies to get and set primitive types from line cells.

      • getStringCellValue

        public static String getStringCellValue(Line line,
                                        String cellName)
        Utility function that gets the string cell value of the specified cell.
        Parameters:
        line - The line to get value from
        cellName - The name of the cell to get
        Returns:
        Value of the specified cell. If the cell exists but contains an empty cell, this method returns an empty string.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - if the line does not have any cell with the specified name. This happens when the schema does not specify any cell with this name.
        See Also:
        getNonEmptyStringCellValue(Line, String), Line.getNonEmptyCell(String), Line.getCell(String)

      • getNonEmptyStringCellValue

        public static Optional<String> getNonEmptyStringCellValue(Line line,
                                                          String cellName)
        Utility function that gets a non empty string cell value of the specified cell.
        Parameters:
        line - The line to get value from
        cellName - The name of the cell to get
        Returns:
        The optional value of the specified cell, not present if there is no such cell or if the cell was an empty string.
        See Also:
        getStringCellValue(Line, String), Line.getNonEmptyCell(String), Line.getCell(String)

        public static Optional<Number> getNumberCellValue(Line line,
                                                  String cellName)
                                           throws IllegalStateException,
                                                  NumberFormatException

        cellName - The name of the cell to get.

        public static int getIntCellValue(Line line,
                                  String cellName,
                                  int defaultValue)
                           throws NumberFormatException
        Utility function that gets the integer cell value of the specified cell. If the specified cell does not exist, the defaultValue is returned. Tries to parse an integer value if cell is not of type NumberCell. Throws a NumberFormatException if the value is not a parsable integer.

        line - The line to get from
        cellName - The name of the cell to get
        defaultValue - Default value that will be returned if the cell does not exist or does not have any value.
        Returns:
        The integer value of the cell with the specified name.
        Throws:
        NumberFormatException - If the cell could not be converted into an integer value
        See Also:
        getNumberCellValue(Line, String)

      • getEnumCellValue

        public static <E extends Enum<E>> Optional<E> getEnumCellValue(Line line,
                                                               String cellName,
                                                               Class<E> enumClass)
                                                        throws IllegalArgumentException
        Utility function that gets the enum cell value of the specified cell. If the specified cell does not exist, the supplied default value is returned.
        Parameters:
        line - The line to get from
        cellName - The name of the cell to get
        enumClass - The class of the enum to convert the value into.
        Returns:

        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If the cell does not exist
        IllegalArgumentException - If the enum type of the defaultValue does not have an enum constant with the name equal to the value of the specified cell.

      • getEnumCellValue

        public static <E extends Enum<E>> E getEnumCellValue(Line line,
                                                     String cellName,
                                                     E defaultValue)
                                              throws IllegalArgumentException
        Utility function that gets the Enum cell value of the specified cell. If the specified cell does not exist, the supplied default value is returned.
        Parameters:
        line - The line to get from
        cellName - The name of the cell to get
        defaultValue - Default value that will be returned if the cell does not exist or does not have any value.
        Returns:
        The enum cell value if the cell exist and can be converted to an enum. Returns the defaultValue if the cell does not exist.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - If the enum type of the defaultValue does not have an enum constant with the name equal to the value of the specified cell.
